SpringBoot Day 1
================
Product - Bread & Butter

Server: Amazon.com
Frontend:
1. UI - User Experience (UX) - 5%
Backend:
2. Middle layer / Web Services / RESTful APIs 85%
	- Endpoints
	- Bussiness
	- Data Access Layer - DAO <- Queries (JDBC)
3. DB (select * from iphone 14 table) - 10%

Frontend: HTML(index.html), CSS/bootstrap, JS
	- ReactJS, VueJS

Backend:
Middle layer - SpringBoot framework
DB - SQL - Oracle, MySql, SQLDevelop
   	- JSON - MongoDB, CosmosDB, DynamoDB, ScyllaDB

Requirements Spring Boot:
IDE - Spring STS (Eclipse) https://spring.io/tools
Java - 17

Dependency Injection:
- Without using new keyword, spring can create object (singleton), if we use @Component. (ConfigurableApplicationContext obj getBean(classname.class))
- @Autowired is also do dependency injection

Keywords/Annotaions:
https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/docs/current/reference/htmlsingle/
https://www.javatpoint.com/spring-boot-annotations
- @SpringBootApplication - on top of the class has main method. And inside main method there should be SpringApplication.run(currentclassname.class, args);
- @RestController - Refer to rest api endpoints on top of the class
- @GetMapping - GET request on top of method
- @Scope(value = "prototype") after @Component - we use it not to create objects as singleton
